                <p><g type="cross">+</g> ἐνθάδε κεῖ<lb break="no"/>τε ἡ μακαρία <lb/>Στεφανία
                    ἀνα<lb break="no"/>παεῖσα <expan><abbr>μ<hi rend="superscript">η</hi></abbr><ex>νὸς</ex></expan> Λώου,<lb/> κατὰ
                            <expan><abbr>Ἄραβ</abbr><ex>ας</ex></expan>
                    <num value="19">ιθ᾿</num><lb/>
                    <expan><abbr>ἰνδ</abbr><ex>ικτιῶνος</ex></expan>
                    <num value="4">δ᾿</num></p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Here lies the blessed Stephania, who came to rest in the month of Loios according
                    to the Arabs 19, indiction 4.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>Date is uncertain: the 19th Arab year was not the fourth indiction; location is
                    uncertain: the museum note is not clear whether the inscription came from Hebron
                    or Beersheba.</p>
            </div>
